tasks/snow_update.yml
---
- name: Validate ServiceNow endpoint settings
  assert:
    that:
      - snow_instance_url | length > 0
      - snow_update_path | length > 0
    fail_msg: "snow_instance_url and snow_update_path must be set."

- name: Build headers
  set_fact:
    snow_headers: >-
      {{
        {
          'Accept': 'application/json',
          'Content-Type': 'application/json'
        }
        | combine(
            (snow_bearer_token | length > 0)
            | ternary({'Authorization': 'Bearer ' ~ snow_bearer_token}, {})
          )
      }}

- name: POST update to ServiceNow
  uri:
    url: "{{ snow_instance_url }}{{ snow_update_path }}"
    method: POST
    headers: "{{ snow_headers }}"
    body_format: json
    body: "{{ snow_body_info }}"
    validate_certs: "{{ snow_validate_certs }}"
    force_basic_auth: "{{ (snow_user | length > 0) and (snow_password | length > 0) }}"
    user: "{{ snow_user | default(omit) }}"
    password: "{{ snow_password | default(omit) }}"
    status_code: [200, 201, 202, 204]
  no_log: true
How it works (quick explanation)
Build phase (localhost)
Reads jvm_restart.envs
For each payload host, uses add_host to add it to:
wsjvm_restart_targets (umbrella group)
wsjvm_restart_targets_<env> (env group)
Adds connection vars so AWX can SSH even if your inventory only has localhost:
ansible_host, ansible_connection
Execute phase (parallel per host)
Runs only on wsjvm_restart_targets
Batches by profile:
serverStatus.sh -all once before
start stopped JVMs (3 tasks)
restart started JVMs (3 tasks stop + PID poll + 3 tasks start)
serverStatus.sh -all once after (wait until all started)
record results (include_tasks loop)
Notify phase (localhost)
Collects all jvm_results from target hosts
Builds failed_hosts
Posts one update to ServiceNow
Important AWX settings (so this works with localhost-only inventory)
Limit: empty
Ask limit on launch: OFF
Machine credential must allow SSH to the payload hosts

If you want, I can also add a single variable like wsjvm_os_is_aix: true to auto-set safe defaults (pipelining/remote_tmp) and add extra debug around become failures.
